---
title: Aubergine Fatteh with chilli garlic yoghurt and roast baby potatoes
description: Fatteh is a dish that consists of pieces of flatbread covered with a range of delicious ingredients depending on what region you're in. The recipe is Egyptian and Levantine in origin, and as such is often bursting with middle eastern flavours. This veggie version features chickpeas, aubergine and a spicy garlic yoghurt.
